00:00:51,118 --> 00:00:54,853
narrator: the first aluminum boat was launched as a simple skiff 

4
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:56,856
in the middle of the last century.      

5
00:00:56,858 --> 00:00:58,857
fishermen loved the lightweight hull      

6
00:00:58,859 --> 00:01:01,927
because it could be pulled in 
and out of the water more easily

7
00:01:01,929 --> 00:01:03,863
than the wooden boats of the day.          

8
00:01:03,865 --> 00:01:07,066
decades later, aluminum boats have gone high-end,      

9
00:01:07,068 --> 00:01:09,969
but they still have that lightweight appeal.    

10
00:01:14,609 --> 00:01:17,943
since aluminum hulls aren't as heavy as other types,    

11
00:01:17,945 --> 00:01:22,147
these boats will go farther on a tank of gas.       

12
00:01:22,149 --> 00:01:24,550
they make them from high-grade aluminum    

13
00:01:24,552 --> 00:01:26,218
that's corrosion-resistant.  

14
00:01:26,220 --> 00:01:28,087
rollers flatten the metal,   

15
00:01:28,089 --> 00:01:31,691
and a blade called a slitter cuts it to length.       

16
00:01:34,028 --> 00:01:36,562
a computer-guided router then makes precise cuts     

17
00:01:36,564 --> 00:01:39,498
to produce parts that will fit together perfectly,  

18
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:42,835
like this bracket to reinforce the stern.    

19
00:01:45,907 --> 00:01:47,839
they cut the boat's larger components       

20
00:01:47,841 --> 00:01:50,042
with a computerized plasma torch.         

21
00:01:50,044 --> 00:01:54,179
it can cut a wider path than the router.        

22
00:01:54,181 --> 00:01:57,783
they transfer the cut parts to a pallet.          

23
00:01:57,785 --> 00:02:00,653
this is the boat's bottom panel.

24
00:02:04,125 --> 00:02:06,125
a long piece of aluminum will be the gunnel,      

25
00:02:06,127 --> 00:02:08,861
which is the upper edge of the hull.          

26
00:02:08,863 --> 00:02:11,063
they bend it around a wooden template    

27
00:02:11,065 --> 00:02:13,833
to give it the correct curvature.     

28
00:02:18,539 --> 00:02:22,475
next, they reinforce the bow with an extra plate of aluminum

29
00:02:22,477 --> 00:02:24,276
to withstand pounding waves.  

30
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:27,546
they brace the other end with numerous stiffeners    

31
00:02:27,548 --> 00:02:29,682
and screw them into place.   

32
00:02:29,684 --> 00:02:32,151
the screws act as a clamping system,     

33
00:02:32,153 --> 00:02:35,821
until the parts of the boat can be permanently attached.  

34
00:02:35,823 --> 00:02:38,423
a line of caulking helps waterproof the seam   

35
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:40,826
between the hull and the back of the boat,   

36
00:02:40,828 --> 00:02:42,928
called the transom.      

37
00:02:45,232 --> 00:02:47,700
again,             
screws hold everything together,

38
00:02:47,702 --> 00:02:50,903
as the painstaking clamping continues.           

39
00:02:50,905 --> 00:02:53,506
they join the two sides of the bow           

40
00:02:53,508 --> 00:02:56,342
and hold the ends together with a vise grip.       

41
00:02:58,579 --> 00:03:02,247
this strip of aluminum will act
as the spine of the bow.    

42
00:03:02,249 --> 00:03:04,383
it's called the brace plate.  

43
00:03:04,385 --> 00:03:07,319
more screws tack it into position.         

44
00:03:10,925 --> 00:03:15,393
they attach the sides to the rest of the hull.    

45
00:03:15,395 --> 00:03:18,797
now they drill hundreds of holes
along the seams        

46
00:03:18,799 --> 00:03:20,265
and plug them with rivets.   

47
00:03:20,267 --> 00:03:22,134
they extract the clamping screws

48
00:03:22,136 --> 00:03:26,071
and fill their holes with more rivets.       

49
00:03:26,073 --> 00:03:29,709
they install the gunnels on the rim of the hull.     

50
00:03:31,945 --> 00:03:34,346
and now it's time for the tank test.       

51
00:03:34,348 --> 00:03:38,451
they lower the boat into a tank 
to confirm that it's watertight.

52
00:03:39,754 --> 00:03:42,822
if they find any leaks in all those rivets,      

53
00:03:42,824 --> 00:03:45,624
they'll make the necessary adjustments.   

54
00:03:45,626 --> 00:03:48,293
they spray foam into the bottoms and sides   

55
00:03:48,295 --> 00:03:49,762
to keep this boat afloat    

56
00:03:49,764 --> 00:03:52,098
in the event that something punctures it.  

57
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:56,835
and then they rough up the surface          

58
00:03:56,837 --> 00:03:58,604
to allow paint to better adhere.

59
00:04:05,780 --> 00:04:07,379
they move to the interior   

60
00:04:07,381 --> 00:04:09,982
and install felt on the storage panels     

61
00:04:09,984 --> 00:04:12,284
to give them a more finished look.     

62
00:04:15,989 --> 00:04:19,258
then they lay the carpeting port to starboard.       

63
00:04:21,461 --> 00:04:25,130
next comes the plastic fuel tank.     

64
00:04:25,132 --> 00:04:29,668
all they have to do is connect the fuel-line hoses 

65
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:34,406
and secure them with a stainless steel collar. 

66
00:04:34,408 --> 00:04:37,209
the dash panel fits onto the front.        

67
00:04:37,211 --> 00:04:38,744
it's pre-wired,        

68
00:04:38,746 --> 00:04:43,148
so they simply connect it to the boat's main wiring harness.

69
00:04:43,150 --> 00:04:48,220
next, they apply lubricant to the motor's propeller shaft.

70
00:04:48,222 --> 00:04:52,023
this allows the propeller to slide on easily.      

71
00:04:52,025 --> 00:04:54,827
they tighten it with a pneumatic ratchet.   

72
00:04:57,565 --> 00:05:00,499
then they hoist the motor onto the stern         

73
00:05:00,501 --> 00:05:02,434
and bolt it into position.   

74
00:05:11,579 --> 00:05:14,579
with the luxurious interior now complete,         

75
00:05:14,581 --> 00:05:17,115
this metal boat bears very little resemblance    

76
00:05:17,117 --> 00:05:20,085
to its utilitarian predecessors.

77
00:05:22,323 --> 00:05:25,591
this particular model doubles as a fishing boat   

78
00:05:25,593 --> 00:05:28,393
and a pleasure craft.     

79
00:05:28,395 --> 00:05:30,796
and it proves that aluminum boats      

80
00:05:30,798 --> 00:05:34,867
are no longer just a basic form of transportation.

